The paper deals with the concept of differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also involves statistical queries and sample complexity, which are topics in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper uses the Hoeffding bound and the Private Multiplicative Weights mechanism, which are concepts in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the accuracy and generalization properties of differential privacy, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.SI).
